(b) You must cause any modified files to carry prominent notices stating
    that You changed the files; and

(c) You must retain, in the Source Code Form of any Modifications that
    You create, all copyright, patent, trademark, and attribution
    notices from the Source Code Form of the Covered Software, excluding
    those notices that do not pertain to any part of the Covered
    Software, and for Modifications created by You, add an appropriate
    attribution notice.
    
(d) You must also duplicate the notice in Exhibit A in each file of the
    Source Code Form of all Modifications created by You.
    
    If it is not possible to put such notice in a particular Source Code
    file due to its structure, then You must include such notice in a
    location (such as a relevant directory file) where a recipient would
    be likely to look for such a notice.

